                                                                                                               Case filed over bridge mishap
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                           Accident site. Telegraph pix                                  
	Patna, Feb. 17: A complaint was lodged today in a Muzaffarpur district court against railway minister Lalu Prasad and five others for the death of four in yesterdays Amgola railway bridge mishap.         
	The deaths occurred when a large and heavy piece of a concrete slab fell on passers-by, including a family, crossing underneath the Amgola over bridge, under the Kazi Mohammed police station area.         
	Ircon director Ajay Sharma, whose firm was awarded the contract for the construction of the over bridge also figures in the case.        
	Complainant S.K. Ojha, a lawyer in the Muzaffarpur court, lodged the cases against persons in question under sections of murder, attempt to murder and negligence of work in the court of chief judicial magistrate J.K. Sinha.         
	The court took cognisance of the matter and directed the officer-in-charge of Kazi Mohammad police station to lodge an FIR and submit an investigation report to the court as early as possible.         
	Four people, including a 10-year-old girl, had died when a portion of the railway bridge caved in crushing the people.         
	I have appealed to the court to try the accused in cases of murder, attempt to murder and negligence, Ojha said, adding: I am confident that the court will eventually maintain my appeal.                                                                                                                                                                           
